header.gameNote: MID CONTINENT CONF TR AT TULSA OK

article.headline: Oral Roberts 75, IUPUI 54
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 25 points to help Oral Roberts to a 75-54 win over IUPUI on Monday in the semifinals of the Mid-Continent Conference tournament. With the win, Oral Roberts (22-10) advances to the tournament championship for the third consecutive year. ORU will face Oakland, which beat Missouri-Kansas City 83-79 in the other semifinal. The Golden Eagles opened the game with an 11-0 run and never trailed. Green, the three-time conference player of the year, went 8-of-16 from the field and 9-of-10 on free throws. Shawn King scored 14 points on 7-of-9 shooting while ORU teammate Adam Liberty added 11 points, five rebounds and five assists. David Barlow led the fourth-seeded Jaguars (15-15) with 16 points and Gary Patterson scored 12. During the opening 6 1/2 minutes, IUPUI went 0-for-11 from the field, and the Golden Eagles held a 26-7 lead with 5 minutes remaining in the half. The Jaguars finished shooting a season-low 29 percent (14-of-48) from the field, while ORU was at 46 percent (27-of-59). The Jaguars, who trailed 37-16 at halftime, cut the lead to 15 early in the second half, but the Golden Eagles responded with a 9-4 run, capped by two Green free throws with 13:39 remaining.
